<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>Law Day • Lawful Day</xh5><p> <i>Law Day</i>—(U.S.) the day established by a resolution of Congress in 1961 to draw attention to the principles of justice and the practice of law: For the last several years the American Bar Association has been sponsoring “<u>Law Day</u>” on May 1.</p><p><i>Lawful Day</i>—(hist.) a day on which the courts sat; a day on which particular kinds of business might be legally done: A calendar indicated the <u>lawful days</u> for legal business, and also the festivals, anniversaries of historical events, etc.</p> </entry>
